          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-1" n="1">The very revrend Dean Smedly,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-2" n="2">Of Dulness, Pride, conceit, a medly,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-3" n="3">Was equally allowd to shine,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-4" n="4">As poet, scholar, &amp; divine.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-5" n="5">With godliness could well dispence,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-6" n="6">Would be a rake, but wanted sense.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-7" n="7">Would strictly after Truth enquire,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-8" n="8">Because he dreaded to come nigh her.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-9" n="9">For liberty no champion bolder,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-10" n="10">He hated balifs at his shoulder,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-11" n="11">To half the world a standing jest,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-12" n="12">A perfect nuisance to the rest.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-13" n="13">For many, (&amp; we may believe him)</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-14" n="14">Had the best wishes they could give him.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-15" n="15">To all mankind a constant friend.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-16" n="16">Provided they had cash to lend.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-17" n="17">One thing he did before he went hence</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-18" n="18">He left us a laconic sentence,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-19" n="19">But cutting of his phrase, &amp; trimming,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-20" n="20">To prove that bishops were old women.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-21" n="21">Poor Envy durst not shew his phiz,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-22" n="22">She was so terrified at his.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-23" n="23">He waded without any shame,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-24" n="24">Through thick &amp; thin, to get a name.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-25" n="25">Tried every sharping trick for bread,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-26" n="26">And after all he seldom sped.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-27" n="27">When Fortune favourd he was nice,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-28" n="28">He never once would cog the dice:</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-29" n="29">But, as she turnd against his play,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-30" n="30">He knew to stop a quartre trois.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-31" n="31">Now sound in mind, &amp; sound in corpus,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-32" n="32">(Says he) though swelld like any porpus.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-33" n="33">Hey heys from hence at forty-four,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-34" n="34">(But by his leave he sinks a score),</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-35" n="35">To the East Indies, there to cheat,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-36" n="36">Till he can purchase an estate;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-37" n="37">Where, after he had filld his chest,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-38" n="38">Hell mount his tub, &amp; preach his best,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-39" n="39">And plainly proves, by dint of text,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-40" n="40">This world is his, &amp; theirs the next.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-41" n="41">Lest that the reader should not know,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-42" n="42">The bank where last he set his toe,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-43" n="43">'Twas Greenwich, There he took a ship,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-44" n="44">And gave his creditors the slip.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-45" n="45">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-46" n="46">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-47" n="47">In seventeen hundred eight &amp; twenty,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-48" n="48">To Fort S<hi rend="superscript">tÌ£</hi> George a pedlar wen he,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-49" n="49">Ye Fates, when all he gets is spent,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-455-083Y-line-50" n="50">Returns him beggar as he went!</l>
          </lg>
